name: Additional powers
text: §201G-465   [Section effective July 1, 2006.  For section effective until June 30, 2006, see above.]  The powers conferred upon the administration by this part shall be in addition and supplemental to the powers conferred upon it by any other law, and nothing in this part shall be construed as limiting any powers, rights, privileges, or immunities conferred upon the administration. [L 1997, c 350, pt of §2; am L 2005, c 196, §26(a)]
